Okuokoko Community Primary School in Okpe Local Government Area of Delta State is in a deplorable shape as children have turned classrooms into football fields, DAILY POST can report. Our Correspondent who went round the school reports that a classroom building has collapsed. The fans in the classrooms and other electrical appliances were also blown off. There are few or no chairs and desks in some of the classrooms. The School is seriously begging for repairs or rehabilitation by the Delta State Government.